<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4448160>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 1‒16. Stilobezzia (Stilobezzia) tobiasi n. sp. Male: 1‒2, 6, 11, 13‒16; Female: 3‒5, 7‒10, 12. 1. Head, dorsal view; 2‒3. Antenna, lateral view; 4. Palpus, lateral view; 5. Mandible, lateral view; 6‒7. Thorax, lateral view; 8‒10. Tarsomere 5, lateral view, 8, fore leg, 9, mid leg, 10, hind leg; 11‒12. Wing, dorsal view, 11, anterior veins; 13. Abdomen, dorsal view. 14‒16. Male genitalia, ventral view. Scales: 1‒5, 8‒15 = 0.1 mm; 6‒7 = 0.5 mm; 16 = 0.4 mm. Abbreviations: aed= aedeagus; bas apo= basal apodeme; goncx= gonocoxite; gonst= gonostylus; lob = finger-like lobe of the gonocoxite; par= paramere; st 9= sternite 9." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4448160/files/figure.png" .

